 Yinka Kolawole in Osogbo The Osun State Governor, Mr. Gboyega Oyetola, has pledged that he would not renege on full payment of workers’ salaries and pension if he is reelected. Oyetola said this yesterday during an engagement programme with members of The Triangular Group of Pensioners in Osogbo. The governor, who was represented by his Special Adviser on Civic Engagement, Mr. Olatunbosun Oyintiloye, described those who were spreading false information that he would stop payment of full salaries as enemies of progress. He said that his priority is to see the state’s workforce happy and productive, said the era of half salaries is gone in the state. Oyetola also assured pensioners in the state that nothing would stop the payment of their monthly pension, adding that their positive contributions to the development of the state would never be forgotten.